[[File:Glove_of_Darth_Vader1.png|thumb|right|250px|[[Trioculus]] recovers the Glove of Darth Vader from a twisted pile of wreckage on [[Dac/Legends|Dac's]] ocean floor]]
{{Quote|No greater symbol of darkness was ever made than this glove &mdash; the gauntlet that once covered Darth Vader's right hand.|[[Rajah Ubooki|Kadann]]|<ref name="Mission from Mount Yoda">''[[Mission from Mount Yoda]]''</ref>}}
The '''Glove of Darth Vader''' was a [[Mandalorian/Legends|Mandalorian]] [[Crushgaunt/Legends|Crushgaunt]] fitted around one of [[Sith Lord/Legends|Lord]] [[Skere Kaan]]'s indestructible [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] [[Sith talisman/Legends|amulets]]. The gauntlet was worn by [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] upon his right hand.<ref name="END">{{Hyperspace|url=hyperspace/member/insideronline/88/indexp2.html|text=''Evil Never Dies: The Sith Dynasties''|int=Evil Never Dies: The Sith Dynasties}}</ref> Although both gloves for [[Darth Vader's armor/Legends|Darth Vader's armor]] contained micronized [[Beskar/Legends|Mandalorian iron]] as a means to deflect direct hits from [[Blaster/Legends|blaster]] bolts (a feature made redundant due to his [[Force power/Legends|Force abilities]]),<ref name="3D Reconstruction Log">''[[Star Wars: Darth Vader: A 3-D Reconstruction Log]]''</ref> the Glove possessed exclusive features compared to the left glove, including grip-augmentation circuitry.

==History==
During the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]], [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] severed Vader's hand with his [[Luke Skywalker's green lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]], and the cybernetic appendage was lost down a shaft in [[Palpatine/Legends|the Emperor's]] [[Emperor's Throne Room/Legends|throne room]] aboard the [[Death Star II/Legends|Death Star]]. The battle station was destroyed shortly afterward, and Vader's glove was presumably lost.<ref name="ROTJ">{{Film|VI}}</ref> The glove survived, however, ensnared within a piece of wreckage that landed on the watery world of [[Dac/Legends|Dac]]; it had been pulled through a [[Wormhole/Legends|wormhole]] created by the explosion of the [[Hypermatter/Legends|hypermatter]] in the Death Star's core.<ref name="GODV">''[[The Glove of Darth Vader]]''</ref>

In [[5 ABY/Legends|5 ABY]], the false [[Prophets of the Dark Side|Prophet of the Dark Side]] known as [[Rajah Ubooki|Kadann]] foretold that the chosen heir to the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] would present himself bearing the Glove of Darth Vader. The former Imperial [[Grand Moff/Legends|Grand Moff]] [[Bertroff Hissa]] took advantage of this alleged prophecy and used it to proclaim a [[mutant]]-[[Human/Legends|Human]] known as [[Trioculus]] as the new [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Galactic Emperor]]. Hissa [[Kessendra Coronation|presented]] Trioculus as the son of the late Emperor Palpatine at the [[Kessendra Stadium]] on [[Kessel/Legends|Kessel]], and Trioculus thereafter embarked upon a mission to recover the glove of Darth Vader.<ref name="GODV" /> The information of the glove supplied to the false Kadann, and by extension, Trioculus and Hissa, was supplied by [[Sate Pestage/Legends|Sate Pestage]]. Although unknown to either party, the motives for Pestage were because Emperor Palpatine had revived himself from his death above Endor, and had planned to use the amulet to quickly amplify his body and restore his powers, as the ordeal left him weakened.<ref name="SPIN Declassified">{{SW|url=news/the-star-wars-spy-game-spin-declassified|text=The ''Star Wars'' Spy Game: SPIN Declassified|int=The Star Wars Spy Game: SPIN Declassified|nolive=1}}</ref>

The gauntlet's value as a symbol was of little use to the three-eyed mutant, but its potential for use as a weapon was considered to be incalculable. It was his belief that the glove was actually a mystical relic that gave its wearer the ability to [[Telekinesis/Legends|telekinetically]] attack others from a distance. Trioculus was ignorant of the fact that this ability was more so an aspect of Darth Vader's aptitude with [[The Force/Legends|the Force]], and had little to do with his glove.

[[File:Glove_of_Darth_Vader2.png|thumb|left|250px|[[MD-5]] examines the Glove of Darth Vader]]

Trioculus recruited an unscrupulous [[Whaladon/Legends|Whaladon]] hunter named [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Dunwell]] to ferry him through the [[Valley of the Giant Oysters]] on Dac. He personally donned a submersible wetsuit and retrieved the glove from a wrecked [[ion deactivator]], left over from the Death Star.<ref name="GODV" />

[[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] heroes [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Gial Ackbar/Legends|Ackbar]] and Luke Skywalker piloted a [[Mon Calamari submersible|Calamarian minisub]] into the valley and intercepted Dunwell's [[Whaladon-hunting submarine|ship]]. Trioculus attempted to use the "power" of Darth Vader's glove against Skywalker, but to no effect. Skywalker survived the attacks and succeeded in destroying Captain Dunwell's ship, though Trioculus escaped with the glove.<ref name="GODV" /> He had his technicians outfit the glove with technology that could simulate Vader's [[Telekinesis/Legends#Force Choke|Force Choke]], but soon abandoned its use after discovering that utilizing it too often resulted in periods of blindness&mdash;as well as withering his hand. Trioculus commanded that his servants create an exact replica of the glove,<ref name="LCOTJ">''[[The Lost City of the Jedi]]''</ref> while the true glove was returned to the false Kadann.<ref name="Zorba Revenge">''[[Zorba the Hutt's Revenge]]''</ref> It was then taken from his corpse by [[Azrakel]], who then used its power to aid him in slaughtering the true Prophets, on [[Bosthirda/Legends|Bosthirda]].<ref name="END" /> After Azrakel's death, the Glove was believed to have fallen into the possession of [[Lumiya]].<ref name="SPIN Declassified" /> The [[Bimm/Legends|Bimm]] [[Merchant/Legends|merchant]] [[Glah Ubooki]] later claimed to possess a glove worn by Darth Vader, but did not specify that it was the Glove itself.<ref name="AJ1">{{JournalCite|1|Glah Ubooki's Strange & Wondrous Imports (article)}}</ref>

